description: Aspose.Diagram is a class library for working with Microsoft Visio files. It allows developers to create new diagrams and work with VSD, VSS, VST, VSX, VTX, VDW and VDX files on ASP.NET web applications, web services and Windows applications. It allows you to open files and manipulate the elements of the diagram, from lines and fills, to more complex elements, and then export to VDX, VSX, VTX, XPS, HTML, image or PDF formats.
releaseNotes:
This release introduces the features, enhancements and bug fixes as detailed below:
	Features
DIAGRAM-23140 - Add export to HTML
DIAGRAM-33173 - Implement rendering various styles of line

Enhancements
DIAGRAM-32525 - [PDF rendering] Support Anti-Aliasing effect
DIAGRAM-26268 - [LINQ support] Add IQueryable interface support for collection classes

Bugs
DIAGRAM-33131 - [PDF Rendering] Dotted and dashed lines are replaced by solid lines in the output PDF
DIAGRAM-33132 - [PDF Rendering] Output PDF is a bit different from the input diagram
DIAGRAM-33176 - [PDF rendering] Tabs are missing from the text area
DIAGRAM-33177 - [PDF rendering] Connectors' arrows are crossing the text
DIAGRAM-33175 - [PDF rendering] Page headers and footers are missing
summary: Aspose.Diagram is a class library for working with Microsoft Visio files.
title: Aspose.Diagram for .NET
